  "body": "I get `ProviderError: method handler crashed` error when I connect to a [Quorum](https://consensys.net/quorum/) network. Connecting with `ethers`  via the regular method works fine.\r\n\r\nError: \r\n```\r\nProviderError: method handler crashed\r\n    at HttpProvider.request (C:\\Projects\\my-project\\node_modules\\hardhat\\internal\\core\\providers\\http.js:50:23)\r\n    at LocalAccountsProvider.request (C:\\Projects\\my-project\\node_modules\\hardhat\\internal\\core\\providers\\accounts.js:117:38)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:93:5)\r\n    at async EthersProviderWrapper.send (C:\\Projects\\my-project\\node_modules\\@nomiclabs\\hardhat-ethers\\internal\\ethers-provider-wrapper.js:11:24)\r\n```\r\n\r\nConnecting to the same Quorum Node via `ethers` that works:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst provider = new ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider(\r\n    MY_QUORUM_NODE_ADDRESS\r\n  );\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error occurs when I run a script with the `HARDHAT_NETWORK` env set for the `hardhat.config.js`. For example, my `hardhat.config.js`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n...\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: '0.8.5',\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {},\r\n    myquorum: {\r\n      url: MY_QUORUM_NODE_ADDRESS,\r\n      chainId: 1101,\r\n      from: '0x0000000....',\r\n      accounts: [\r\n        '0x0000000....',\r\n      ],\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen running the script:\r\n\r\n`HARDHAT_NETWORK=myquorum node scripts/deploy-my-contract.js`\r\n\r\nWhy is this happening with HardHat and not `ethers`?\r\n",
